  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to PRC COVID-19 Response - dedicated support to the management of the isolation facilities for mild COVID-19 patients</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Beneficiaries are mild COVID-19 positive cases, indirect beneficiary are the hospitals as it will allow them to focus on serious COVID-19 cases (reducing stress on bed space)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishment and ongoing running support of COVID19 isolation facilities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hospitals in the Philippines are overwhelmed with the number of COVID19 patients. Bed capacity in many hospitals have reached a critical point and worst case scenario of the COVID19 variant entering the Philippines it could get worse. Part of the challenges faced particularly in Metro Manila are patients being admitted for mild symptoms occupying critical bed space. The PRC is establishing &quot;tent isolation facilities and working with the Depts of Education to use classrooms&quot; as isolation facilities for mild COVID cases reducing the burden on the hospitals</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Metro Manila currently, however situation is fluid and it may be realigned to other cities in the Philippines. In Metro Manila the PRC has already identified 10 isolation facility locations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The PRC will establish or convert existing structures for temporary isolation facilities it will provide ambulance services, set up isolation beds, provide supplementary hot meals, set up showers and latrines, 
It will coordinate with local government units for the establishment of the facilities, costs including establishment of facilities, ongoing running costs and volunteers allowances</narrative>
  </description>
